    "narkk_pages_founder_letter_aEywMR": {
      "type": "narkk-pages-founder-letter",
      "name": "Founder Letter",
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/narkk-philosophy-founder-letter-img.webp",
        "image_position": "center center",
        "heading": "A Letter from Our Founder",
        "uppercase": false,
        "salutation": "Dear customer,",
        "letter_content": "<p>My name is Niranjan. I’m the Creative Principal of narkk, and I want to share something I’ve never said in a brochure or product listing.For four years, I made furniture I wasn’t proud of.</p><p>Not because I didn’t care — but because the market had its own logic. Clients wanted pieces that looked good and lasted just long enough five years, maybe. And I delivered exactly that. Cheaper boards, faster finishes, borrowed designs. The business worked. But every time I walked away, something felt hollow.</p><p>Around the same time, in my own life, things I bought kept failing a phone that slowed after updates, appliances that died just after warranty, earphones that stopped working overnight. I told myself I was unlucky. That I’d picked the wrong products.But standing in my workshop one day, it clicked this wasn’t bad luck. This was the plan.</p><p>Products failing quietly, just past the point of complaint. Replacements framed as upgrades. A system designed to keep us buying.</p>",
        "read_more_label": "read more",
        "padding_top": 120,
        "padding_bottom": 120
      }
    },
